    "created_at": "2015-10-14T05:20:08Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-10-14T05:20:08Z",
    "body": "Should we make the `savePage` accept a callback instead of relying on `will-download` event to get notified when save is done? The latter looks reasonable in Chrome because it is started by user, but it feels strange and inconvenient when used as API.\n"
  },
